        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 3:12PM EDT until June 27 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>SVRPBZ

The National Weather Service in Pittsburgh has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Columbiana County in east central Ohio...
Mercer County in northwestern Pennsylvania...
Western Lawrence County in western Pennsylvania...

* Until 400 PM EDT.

* At 312 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
near Greenville to over Columbiana, or along a line from 15 miles
northeast of Sharpsville to over Columbiana, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
New Castle, Hermitage, Sharon, Columbiana, East Palestine,
Sharpsville, Greenville, Farrell, New Wilmington, Oakwood,
Leetonia, New Castle Northwest, New Waterford, Mercer, New Beaver,
Pulaski, Bessemer, Stoneboro, New Bedford and West Middlesex.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
